==English==

===Noun===
'''experiential advertising''' 

# (Advertising) commercials designed to evoke strong sensory responses from the audience as opposed to pitching a rational sales message.
#:''Commercials that make you want to run to the fridge for a soda or drive to the restaurant for a burger are examples of one type of '''experiential advertising.''''' 
#(Advertising) also known as emotional advertising.



